Question: Decide on a party or event that you want to organize and write details on how you want to organize the event (budget, music, location, guest list, etc.).
Answer:
This is not really my area of expertise, but here goes... If I were to throw a typical party for a bunch of friends I would want to hold it in the country-side where we could have a bonfire. Ideally, food would be provided in the form of bar-be-que. But guests would be free to bring sides and drinks, though some would also be provided. As for a music, a live band would be cool, but not necessary. I don't enjoy the same kinds of music as most people do, so I might defer to the expertise of a DJ. Overall it would not need to be an expensive party.